# Git workflow

When the user asks you to commit changes, push to GitHub immediately after a successful commit unless they explicitly say not to push.

## Which repo to use

- **Brisbane AI CFO** (this repo): commit and push to `https://github.com/llRSll/Brisbane-AI-CFO.git`.
- Deployable app lives in `backup/` (Vercel root directory).
- **Dine For A Dream** (archived): separate project at `C:\Users\ruebe\Coding Projects\Dine For A Dream` → `https://github.com/llRSll/DineForADream2026.git`.

## Push rules

- Use `git push -u origin HEAD` when pushing a new branch
- Use `git push origin <branch>` when pushing to an existing tracked branch
- Do not force-push to main/master unless explicitly requested
